---

## 1. Problem Statement

The Agent Output modal has two issues: (1) The "Summary" tab that previously showed summaries with a selectable dropdown is not displaying because it is conditionally rendered only when a summary exists, and since no `<summary>` tags or saved summary files are present for the given feature, the tab is completely hidden. (2) The "Logs" tab appears empty because the agent output content (`output` state) is empty -- the agent-output.md file either doesn't exist or has no content for the feature, so the LogViewer receives an empty string.

## 2. User Story

As a user, I want the Summary tab to always be visible in the Agent Output modal (showing a helpful empty state when no summaries exist yet) and I want the Logs tab to display all available agent output content, so that I can reliably access these views regardless of the feature's execution state.

## 3. Acceptance Criteria

- **Happy Path (Summary exists)**: GIVEN a feature with at least one saved summary or inline `<summary>` tag, WHEN I open the Agent Output modal, THEN the Summary tab is visible with the dropdown selector and I can view each summary individually.
- **Empty Summary**: GIVEN a feature with no summaries, WHEN I open the Agent Output modal, THEN the Summary tab is still visible in the tab bar and shows a helpful empty state message like "No summary available yet."
- **Logs with content**: GIVEN a feature with agent-output.md containing log content, WHEN I click the Logs tab, THEN the LogViewer renders the parsed log entries.
- **Logs empty**: GIVEN a feature with no agent output, WHEN I click the Logs tab, THEN it shows "No output yet. The agent will stream output here as it works." (existing behavior).
- **Default tab**: GIVEN a feature with no summary, WHEN I open the Agent Output modal, THEN the Plan tab is shown by default (since there's no summary to show).

## 4. Technical Context

| Aspect | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Affected Files | `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/dialogs/agent-output-modal.tsx` |
| Dependencies | None |
| Constraints | Must maintain backward compatibility with existing summary dropdown logic |
| Patterns to Follow | Existing conditional tab rendering pattern in the same file |

## 5. Non-Goals

- Fixing why agent-output.md might be empty for specific features (that's a server-side agent execution issue, not a UI issue)
- Changing the summary saving/fetching API
- Modifying the LogViewer or log-parser logic

## 6. Implementation Tasks

```tasks
## Phase 1: Fix Summary Tab Visibility

- [ ] T001: Make Summary tab always visible in the tab bar, regardless of whether summary content exists | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/dialogs/agent-output-modal.tsx
- [ ] T002: Add empty state for Summary tab content area when no summaries are available | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/dialogs/agent-output-modal.tsx
- [ ] T003: Update default view mode logic so it defaults to 'plan' instead of 'summary' when no summary exists (preventing a blank Summary tab from being the default) | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/dialogs/agent-output-modal.tsx

## Phase 2: Fix Logs Tab Display

- [ ] T004: Ensure the Logs tab renders the LogViewer or appropriate empty state correctly when selected | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/dialogs/agent-output-modal.tsx
```

## 7. Success Metrics

- Summary tab is always visible in the Agent Output modal tab bar
- Summary tab shows dropdown selector when summaries exist, or empty state when none exist
- Logs tab shows parsed log entries when output exists, or a clear empty message when no output
- No regressions in existing functionality (Changes, Raw, Plan tabs unaffected)

## 8. Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|------------|
| Showing Summary tab with no content may confuse users | Add a clear, informative empty state message |
| Default tab change may surprise existing users | Default to 'plan' which is more useful when no summary exists |
